Encoding: UTF-8
Maintainer: Somak Dutta <somakd@iastate.edu>
Description: Compute ridge partial correlation coefficients for each column in a matrix
 and perform model selection based on the extended Bayesian Information Criteria. Users
 provide the matrix of covariates, either in the default matrix format of R or as a sparse
 matrix of type dgCMatrix, and a vector of response variable. Detail of the method is given
 in the manual.
